  <Docs>
    <summary>Context passed to a handler on interruption, allows termination of an application.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>
This class is passed as an argument to event handlers that have attached to the <see cref="E:System.Console.CancelKeyPress" /> event.   
</para>
      <para>
By default, after the interrupt sequence is generated by the user (typically control-c), the application will exit, unless one of the handlers set the <see cref="P:System.ConsoleCancelEventArgs.Cancel" /> property to true.
</para>
    </remarks>
    <since version=".NET 2.0" />
